Compile this code with http://closure-compiler.appspot.com/home
--------------------------------------------
// ==ClosureCompiler==
// @compilation_level ADVANCED_OPTIMIZATIONS
// @formatting pretty_print
// ==/ClosureCompiler==

alert(Foo());

function Foo()
{
  return &quot;test&quot;;
}
--------------------------------------------

Results in a WARNING:

JSC_REFERENCE_BEFORE_DECLARE: Variable referenced before declaration: Foo
at line 1 character 6
alert(Foo());

Expect: no WARNING.

I believe it is quite common and correct for forward references to function
declaration in the same scope (global or within a function).  I'm finding
this type of error is producing a lot of noise in the warning stream when
compiling larger libraries.
